"{\"uid\": \"myrepublica.nagariknetwork.com-news-olympic-women-football-qualifier-nepal-playing-against-bangladesh-today\", \"text\": \"Subscribe Now  KATHMANDU, Nov 13: Nepal and Bangladesh are facing each other in the third game of the Olympic Women Football's Asian qualifier today.  The match is taking place at 2.15 pm Nepali time at the Thunuwa stadium based in Yangon, Myanmar, All Nepal Football Association (ANFA) stated.  Today's game is crucial for Nepal as it will decide whether Nepal qualifies for the second round football journey under this tournament. This match is 'do or die' for Nepal to reach the second leg. Nepal was drawn in the two earlier matches.  Nepal was tied 1-1 with India in the first game and with Myanmar in the second game. Nepal which is in Group 'C' has earned two points from as many matches and is in the third position. Myanmar, which has four points, is in the first position and India with four points is in the second place of the tally. Bangladesh, which has not earned any points, is in the last position.  The game between India and Myanmar also holds significance for Nepal. The two countries are meeting in the second game today. No matter whatever the result of the game between India and Myanmar, Nepal would enter the second leg if it is able to defeat Bangladesh in today's match.  Eighteen teams are contesting in the first leg of the qualifier from Asia aiming for the 2020 Tokyo Olympics. RSS  Ballot Box Revolt: What RSP's breakthrough victory...  Warning, Threat or Opportunity? Nepal's major part...  Granary in crisis: Water politics leave Madhesh pa...  \\\"China stands ready to work with Nepal to carry forward the traditional friendship, deepen practical cooperation and advance bilateral relations\\\", read the statement.  Building Nepal's Digital Future  Fuel shortages in Nepal: A hidden threat to health a...  Second Innings of Balen and Gagan  Who will become Balen's climate pilot?  Three \\\"S\\\" factors-sulabhata (availabilit